title: Did all speed-fixing cameras on two major English routes have been set to 72 MHz in January 2019?
subtitle: A viral social media message warned users in the UK against driving on M1 and M25.
author: Dan MacGuill
vclaim: In early January 2019, all speed cameras were activated on the M1 and M25 highways in England simultaneously, with a standard speed of 72 miles per hour.
